    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1836 the Harmony Manufacturing Company, later known as Harmony Mills, began operations, cementing Cohoes’ textile legacy.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cohoes%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The historic Cohoes Falls, a 65‑foot waterfall, was first noted by indigenous peoples and later became the city’s most famous landmark.",
